The paper deals with problems related to graph theory, specifically identifying codes, locating-dominating sets, and resolving sets. These topics are commonly studied in the sub-categories of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), Graph Theory (cs.GT), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). However, since the paper focuses on lower bounds and algorithms for specific classes of graphs (interval graphs, unit interval graphs, permutation graphs, and cographs), it is more likely to be classified under cs.DM, cs.DS, and cs.CG.
